video:video.video:title: Iranian travellers cross into Turkey to be able to keep working around internet blackout
video:video.video:description: Iranians crossing into Turkey said on Friday they were making short jaunts to the neighboring country to get around communications blackouts in Iran, but the border crossing in Turkey's eastern province of Van has not seen a major influx of Iranians fleeing the unrest in their country.

video:video.video:title: US military visits contested area in northern Syria
video:video.video:description: A U.S. military delegation arrived in a contested area of northern Syria on Friday following rising tensions between the Syrian government and a Kurdish-led force that controls much of the northeast.

video:video.video:title: Pets in Madrid receive blessings marking Feast of Saint Anthony
video:video.video:description: Dozens of pet owners took their animals to church on a damp Saturday morning where Catholic priests blessed them on the Day of St Anthony, the patron saint of animals.

video:video.video:title: High electricity prices and Trump dislike of cheap green power will hurt GOP, activist predicts
video:video.video:description: Longtime climate activist Bill McKibben finds hope in solar energy despite the Trump administration rolling back environmental regulations and freezing offshore wind projects.

video:video.video:description: A protest was held in Denmark's capital Copenhagen on Saturday in support of Greenland, amid US President Donald Trump's insistence that the U.S. should control the self-governing island.

video:video.video:title: Syrian forces enter northern towns as Kurdish fighters withdraw from Deir Hafer in Aleppo
video:video.video:description: Syrian government forces entered two northern towns Saturday morning after the command of Kurdish-led fighters said it would evacuate the area in an apparent move to avoid conflict.

video:video.video:description: Families from one of the last remaining Palestinian Bedouin villages in the dusty corridor between Ramallah and Jericho packed up and prepared to flee from their homes on Friday.

video:video.video:title: Delcy Rodriguez says Venezuela's oil will be used to enrich the country
video:video.video:description: Venezuela's acting president Delcy Rodriguez, addressed the nation on Friday following a meeting with the National Council for Productive Economy and called for serenity as the government prepares for key reforms.
